# Nexus Fleet Control — Detailed Project Report

## 1. Project Overview

**Nexus Fleet Control** is a full-stack web application for managing a fleet of robots in real-time. It provides live telemetry tracking, mission planning with custom routes on uploaded maps, multi-user role-based access, and a modern, multi-language dashboard (English, Hindi, Kannada).

---

## 2. Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| **Frontend** | React 19 + Vite 7 | SPA framework and dev server |
| **Canvas Rendering** | Konva.js + react-konva | Interactive 2D map and robot visualization |
| **Internationalization** | i18next + react-i18next | Multi-language support (EN, HI, KN) |
| **Auth (Client)** | Supabase Auth SDK | User login, signup, and OTP verification |
| **Backend** | Node.js + Express 5 + TypeScript | REST API server |
| **Real-time** | WebSocket (ws library) | Bi-directional telemetry and commands |
| **Database** | PostgreSQL (Supabase-hosted) | Persistent storage for users, robots, telemetry |
| **ORM / Query** | pg (node-postgres) | Direct SQL queries via connection pool |
| **Security** | Helmet, CORS, bcryptjs, JOSE (JWT) | HTTP hardening, password hashing, token verification |
| **BaaS** | Supabase | Auth, DB hosting, Row-Level Security, Storage (maps) |

