## 4. Entry Points

### Backend Entry Point — [index.ts](file:///c:/Users/vinit/Desktop/Robot-Dashboard/backend/src/index.ts)
- Initializes Express with CORS, Helmet, and JSON middleware.
- Mounts routes: `/auth`, `/users`, `/robots`.
- Creates HTTP server and attaches the WebSocket server.
- Starts listening on port 5000 (from `.env`).

### Frontend Entry Point — [main.jsx](file:///c:/Users/vinit/Desktop/Robot-Dashboard/frontend/src/main.jsx)
- Imports global CSS and the `i18n.js` configuration.
- Renders `<App />` inside `<StrictMode>`.

### Robot Simulator — [simulate-robot.ts](file:///c:/Users/vinit/Desktop/Robot-Dashboard/backend/src/simulate-robot.ts)
- CLI tool: `npx ts-node src/simulate-robot.ts <API_KEY>`.
- Connects to the WebSocket server using the robot's API key.
- Sends telemetry every 1 second (battery, CPU, temperature, pose).
- Follows waypoints when a `start_mission` command is received (waits 3s at each waypoint).

---

## 5. Main Components

### 5.1 Authentication — [LoginPage.jsx](file:///c:/Users/vinit/Desktop/Robot-Dashboard/frontend/src/components/LoginPage.jsx)
- Handles **login** (via Supabase `signInWithPassword`) and **signup** (with email OTP verification).
- After signup, users must be approved by an admin before they can access the dashboard.
- Multi-language support via `useTranslation()`.

### 5.2 Dashboard Layout — [Dashboard.jsx](file:///c:/Users/vinit/Desktop/Robot-Dashboard/frontend/src/components/Dashboard.jsx)
- Sidebar with navigation: Home, Tracker, Clearance (admin-only), Profile.
- **Language Switcher** dropdown in the header (English / Hindi / Kannada).
- Renders the active tab content in the main viewport.

### 5.3 Home Tab — [HomeTab.jsx](file:///c:/Users/vinit/Desktop/Robot-Dashboard/frontend/src/components/tabs/HomeTab.jsx)
- Fleet overview with robot health scores, status indicators, and quick actions.
- Robot creation form (admin-only) which generates a unique API key for the robot.
- Health score calculated from battery, CPU, and temperature telemetry.

### 5.4 Live Tracker Tab — [TrackerTab.jsx](file:///c:/Users/vinit/Desktop/Robot-Dashboard/frontend/src/components/tabs/TrackerTab.jsx)
This is the most complex component, combining:
- **Map Selection**: Upload and select maps from Supabase Storage.
- **Route Editor** ([RouteEditor.jsx](file:///c:/Users/vinit/Desktop/Robot-Dashboard/frontend/src/components/Tracker/RouteEditor.jsx)): A Konva canvas where users click to place named waypoints (P1, P2…) and draw routes.
- **Mission Controls** ([MissionControls.jsx](file:///c:/Users/vinit/Desktop/Robot-Dashboard/frontend/src/components/Tracker/MissionControls.jsx)): Select a robot, save/load routes, and start/stop missions.
- **Fleet Sidebar**: Live status metrics (Online, Total, Standby, Tracking) and per-robot telemetry cards.

### 5.5 Admin Verification — [AdminVerification.jsx](file:///c:/Users/vinit/Desktop/Robot-Dashboard/frontend/src/components/tabs/AdminVerification.jsx)
- Lists all registered users with their verification status.
- Admin can approve or reject new user registrations.
- Updates user metadata in Supabase.

### 5.6 WebSocket Server — [ws.server.ts](file:///c:/Users/vinit/Desktop/Robot-Dashboard/backend/src/websocket/ws.server.ts)
The heart of the real-time system:
- **Dual Authentication**: Robots authenticate via API key (bcrypt comparison); Users authenticate via Supabase JWT (JOSE verification).
- **Client Registries**: Maintains separate `userClients` and `robotClients` sets for efficient broadcasting.
- **Telemetry Flow**: Robot → WS Server → DB (persist) → Broadcast to authorized users.
- **Command Flow**: User → WS Server → Access control check → Forward to robot socket.

